<DIV TYPE="slide"><HEAD>Reasons not to use SGML or TEI</HEAD>
<P>Several reasons are advanced for not using TEI encoding.<LIST>
<ITEM><Q REND="inline" TYPE="inline">There isn't any software</Q></ITEM>
<ITEM><Q REND="inline" TYPE="inline">It's too complicated; I want
something simpler</Q></ITEM>
<ITEM><Q REND="inline" TYPE="inline">It's too simple: It doesn't do what I need</Q></ITEM>
<ITEM><Q REND="inline" TYPE="inline">There isn't any typesetting
(database, editing, network publishing ...) software for SGML</Q></ITEM>
<ITEM><Q REND="inline" TYPE="inline">SGML is a flawed formal
language</Q></ITEM>
<ITEM><Q REND="inline" TYPE="inline">TEI is an assault on my
intellectual freedom</Q></ITEM></LIST> Need it be said that these are
not all plausible?</P></DIV>
<DIV TYPE="slide"><HEAD>For More Information</HEAD>
<LIST><ITEM>email to tei@uic.edu</ITEM>
<ITEM>subscribe to TEI-L@uicvm.uic.edu</ITEM>
<ITEM>read comp.text.sgml</ITEM>
<ITEM>attend annual SGML conferences organized by Graphic
Communications Association</ITEM>
